      "instruction": "<p>Once the onion has softened, increase the heat to medium-high and add the<strong> lamb mince</strong></p><p>Cook for 4 min until browned, breaking the mince up with a wooden spoon as you go</p><p>Once browned, crumble the<strong> chicken stock cube<span class=\"text-danger\">[s] </span></strong>into the pan with the<strong> tomato paste</strong> and <strong>baharat</strong> and cook for 2 min</p><p>Add 100ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[150ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> and cook for a further 5 min or until the lamb has crisped</p>",
